  <brief_title>Local Application of Autologous Bone Marrow Cells for Treatment of Chronic Diabetic Ulcers</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Heidelberg University</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Heidelberg University</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Bone marrow cells were previously shown to enhance wound healing in experimental diabetes. In
      this pilot study, patients with chronic diabetic ulcers not healing under conventional
      therapy, will be treated with local application of autologous bone marrow cells.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
